            </p>
            <br>

            <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">I-5 Express Ramp Shutdown: A Week of Chaos</h3>
            <p>
              On May 25, 2025, copper wire theft disabled ramp meters on I-5 northbound from I-90 in Seattle. Without the meters, <a href="https://www.kiro7.com/news/local/we-cant-keep-up-copper-wire-thieves-plague-roadways-shut-down-i-5-express-ramp/6RVDRIBJTBDX7DVUZ2MTH373WI/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">congestion worsened for more than a week</a>. Along SR-167, SR-18, and SR-518, Washington State Patrol detectives sought public help after copper theft from WSDOT junction boxes in King County exceeded <strong>$100,000 in combined wire, tools, and damage</strong>.
            </p>
            <br>

            <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Comcast Network Down: Thousands Without Service in Pierce County</h3>
